    <p>Luzon refers to the northernmost islands of the Philippines. Lowlanders found in Luzon enjoyed prosperous trade routes, which the Spanish took advantage of when they established their center of power in Manila. To this day, Luzon remains the
      economic center of the Philippines and is the most populated of the three major regions.</p>

