      <h2>Tagalog</h2>
      <p>They are the most well-known Filipino ethnolinguistic group. The word Tagalog derives from "taga-ilog" meaning people of the river. They are native speakers of Tagalog and its many dialects. The modern Manila dialect is the established
        national language, known as "Pilipino". They once used Bayabyin, which is the most well-known of the Filipino scripts. The Tagalogs had centers of power in Old Tondo and Maynila. The Laguna Copper Plate Inscription belongs to them. Before
