    <h1 data-toggle="modal" data-target="#image-modal">Visayas</h1>
    <p>Visayas is the region found in the middle of the Philippines. The two major groups found in Visayas are the <a tabindex="0" class="italicized info-pop" role="button" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" data-content="According to local lore, it was a confederation of groups originally from Srivijaya (Modern-day Indonesia) founded by 10 datus led by the famed Datu Puti">Madja-As</a> and the <a tabindex="0" class="italicized info-pop" role="button" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" data-content="Rajanate circle of influence centered in Cebu">Sugbu Visayans</a>. Visayans were the first people the Spanish encountered and had intricate tattoos signifying social
      status and achievements, earning them the name <span class="italicized">Pintados</span> or the painted ones.</p>

