      <h2>Cebuano</h2>
      <p>The kingdom of Cebu was founded by Sri Lumay, also known as Rajah Lumaya, of the Sumatran Chola Dynasty during the 13th Century. He and his descendants settled islands throughout Visayas and often warred against Muslim raiders. Under the
        rule of his grandson, Rajah Humabon, the Cebuanos enjoyed a prosperous life with the capital Sibo (meaning trade center) controlling major trade routes. They used a writing form called Kudlit-Badlit, speak Cebuano, and are considered Sugbu Visayans.
        Cebuanos were the first people to ally with the Spanish in exchange for dealing with Humabon's rival, Datu Lapu Lapu, from the neighboring island of Mactan. When Magellan's men failed, the Cebuanos drove off the remaining Spanish forces and
        would be hostile upon their return twenty years later.</p>
